    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-12T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="632"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d632">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.00/846: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in El Salvador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MWJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McCafferty</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-12T15:00:00-06:00"
                            >February 12, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:26 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. The Legislative Assembly today named the following designates: <persName
                        corresp="#p_GCFC1">Colonel Fidel Cristino Garay</persName>, Commandant of
                    the Department of San Miguel, as First Designate; <persName corresp="#p_FCCB1"
                        >Colonel Carlos Borromeo Flores</persName>, Under Secretary of Fomento, as
                    Second Designate; and <persName corresp="#p_PGAJ1">General Alberto J.
                        Pinto</persName>, Commandant of the Department of Santa Ana as Third
                    Designate. It appears that none of these are barred from recognition by the 1923
                    treaty. Further details will follow.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Guatemala, Tegucigalpa, San José and Managua.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">McCafferty</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
